ion passes.\n     2\t//!\n     3\t//! Two tiers of compaction work together to e
xtend useful session length:\n     4\t//!\n     5\t//! - **Microcompaction** run
s every turn as a cheap in-place pass. It replaces\n     6\t//!   expired tool r
esults with cleared markers, freeing tokens without a model call.\n     7\t//!\n
    8\t//! - **Full compaction** fires when token usage crosses a configurable t
hreshold.\n     9\t//!   It summarizes conversation history via a model call and
re-injects critical\n    10\t//!   files that may have been discarded.\n    11\t
//!\n    12\t//! Microcompaction delays the need for full compaction, and full c
ompaction\n    13\t//! resets the context for continued productive work.\n    14
\t\n    15\tuse std::collections::HashMap;\n    16\t\n    17\tuse jiff::SignedDu
ration;\n    18\t\n    19\tuse hermeneus::types::ToolResultType;\n    20\t\n    
21\tpub(crate) mod full;\n    22\tpub(crate) mod micro;\n    23\tpub(crate) mod 
prompts;\n    24\t\n    25\t/// Per-tool-type TTL configuration for microcompact
ion.\n    26\t///\n    27\t/// Determines how long tool results remain before be
